content.description:
Southside is a 25 FT peace of slanted granite with various cracks and knobs. It has a challenging start with next to no holds but as the farther you go the easier the climb be comes. there is no fixed protection so you will need to bring your own nut and cams to top rope there are also some trees and rock you can top rope from.



Southside sticks out a fair bit and is easy to notice on the trail. its about 40 feet off the trail at half way to your right there is also a small bolder in front of southside. You can see Southside from the second trail marker after the stairs.

There are no fixed bolts you will need to bring your own nuts cams and top rope set up. Sections can be bouldered with a mat.

Mill cove trail is can be windy and cold so make sure you check the weather before going. Mill cove trail is 165 FT above sea level it's across route 310 from Louil Hill. it is a granite hill with two main faces and a couple of smaller boulders.  The trail is a short (< 1km) but is up hill the first main face is only 20 or so feet of trail it can be seen on the right of the trail.   There is another face on the east side of the hill from the lookout.
